<title>Loops and Strings</title>


<introduction>
<p>
Computers are often used to automate repetitive tasks, such as searching for text in documents.
Repeating tasks without making errors is something that computers do well and people do poorly.
</p>

<p>
In this chapter, you'll learn how to use <c>while</c> and <c>for</c> loops to add repetition to your code.
We'll also take a first look at <c>String</c> methods and solve some interesting problems.
</p>
